ENTRY       EC 4.1.2.41                 Enzyme
NAME        vanillin synthase;
            3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propionyl-CoA:vanillin lyase (acetyl-CoA-forming)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-carbon lyases;
            Aldehyde-lyases
SYSNAME     3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA vanillin-lyase (acetyl-CoA-forming)
REACTION    3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA = vanillin + acetyl-CoA [RN:R05773]
ALL_REAC    R05773
SUBSTRATE   3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA
PRODUCT     vanillin [CPD:C00755];
            acetyl-CoA [CPD:C00024]
COMMENT     Involved, together with EC 4.2.1.101 trans-feruloyl-CoA hydratase, in the production of vanillin from trans-ferulic acid. Vanillin is converted to vanillate by EC 1.2.1.67 vanillin dehydrogenase.
HISTORY     EC 4.1.2.41 created 2000
